This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump in the East Room of the White House. He starts by expressing condolences to the people of California affected by wildfires and the victims of the mass shooting in Las Vegas, as well as those affected by hurricanes Harvey, Irma, and Maria. He then welcomes the Pittsburgh Penguins, the two-time defending Stanley Cup champions, to the White House. He praises the team's achievements and individual players, and highlights their contributions to the community, including their support for local charities and relief efforts in Puerto Rico and Las Vegas. He encourages the team to strive for a three-peat in the upcoming season and concludes by emphasizing the values of dedication, discipline, and hard work.